---

olive oil
1 potato
1 carrot
1 beetroot
1 sachet Brown Mustard Seeds
1 packet salmon
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Mango Mayonnaise
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced. Cut potato and carrot into bite-sized chunks. Cut beetroot into small chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle over brown mustard seeds, season with salt and toss to coat. Spread out evenly, the roast until tender, 20-25 minutes. Set aside to cool slightly.

TIP: Beetroot stays firm when cooked. It's done when you can pierce it with a fork.

• While veggies are roasting, combine Mumbai spice blend and a drizzle of olive oil in a medium bowl. Add salmon, season with salt and toss to combine.
• When veggies have 5 minutes cook time remaining, heat a large frying pan with a drizzle of olive oil over a medium-high heat. When oil is hot, cook salmon, skin-side down, until just cooked through, 2-4 minutes each side.

TIP: The spice blend will char slightly in the pan, this adds to the flavour!

• Add baby spinach leaves and a drizzle of white wine vinegar to roasted veggies and gently toss to combine. Season to taste.

• Divide Mumbai-spiced salmon and roasted root veggie toss between plates.
• Serve with mango mayonnaise.